een crown whereas the forehead in the female is the same colour as the crown. The rest of the upper parts are rather dark green tinged with yellow. The wings and tail are brownish-black. The throat and breast are darkish grey and the belly is a slightly paler grey. The beak is black, the eye red and the legs reddish. The juvenile is similar to the adult but has grey or buffy tones mixed into the general hue of the plumage. Ecology The habitat of the African piculet is mainly lowland secondary forest. It is an active bird often seen flitting from place to place in pairs or threesomes, and sometimes joining mixed species flocks. It forages through the lower storeys of trees, bushes and dense vegetation. It is a relative of the woodpecker, and despite its small size, hammers its beak into branches and splits stems to get at beetle larvae. It also gleans other insects but seems uninterested in ants. Breeding has been observed between June and February in various parts of its range. The nest is built within 5 metres (16 ft) of the ground and the clutch size is usually two. Both parents are involved in raising the young. References", "shortSummary": "The African piculet (Verreauxia africana), sometimes placed in the genus Sasia, is a species of bird in the family Picidae. It is the only…", "locations": ["安哥拉", "喀麦隆", "中非共和國", "刚果共和国", "刚果民主共和国", "科特迪瓦", "赤道几内亚", "加蓬", "加纳", "利比里亚", "乌干达"], "lat": -12.5, "lng": 18.5, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/49/Sasia_africana_%28YPM_ORN_100653%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-verreauxia", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-verreauxia-africana", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-verreauxia", "species": "taxonomy-species-verreauxia-africana"}, "expandable": true, "x": -382.11, 